news.title: Global slowdown blues to stall demand growth for office space this fiscal: Crisil
news.para: According to Crisil Ratings the inherent strengths of the Indian market and increasing shift to return to office, however, should help demand pick up over the medium term, keeping credit profiles of office asset owners stable.

news.title: Global Capability Centres to lease 60-62 million sq ft space in 2023-25 across top six cities: Report
news.para: Global Capability Centres are now leasing larger offices with the potential to scale up in the future. Availability and cost of talent, real estate, and supporting regulatory framework aid GCCs expansion in India.

news.title: Haryana government to refund development fees of Rs 5.19 crore to 1,588 property owners
news.para: The government made this decision upon becoming aware of the situation. As a result, a total of 1588 property owners will receive a refund.

news.title: New colonies spring up in Jaipur, wait for roads continues
news.para: Villagers in the area said the sitting BJP legislator, Satish Poonia, who is seeking re-election in Amber, has visited them several times in the last couple years.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates 4,272 flats built at cost of Rs 453.67 crore
news.para: ​The chief minister also inaugurated a newly constructed multistoried apartment housing of 32 units, constructed at a cost of Rs 31.26 crore, in Tirunelveli district on Monday.

news.title: PWD to take a second shot at installing over 1,000 streetlights in Delhi
news.para: According to officials, these streetlights are being installed as part of the Chief Minister's streetlight project. Bids were called earlier also but they could not attract many bidders.

news.title: Gujarat: 80 Narmada resettlement colonies to be part of villages
news.para: Eighty resettlement colonies will be included in villages of Bharuch, Narmada, Chhota Udepur, Vadodara, Kheda and Panchmahal districts, an official statement said.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Slum dwellers reluctant to move into affordable houses
news.para: “The apartments in the housing projects have a built up area of 300 to 320 square feet, which is too small for even a family of three to live comfortably,” Pratap Sahu, president, All Odisha Basti Surakhya Manch, said.

news.title: Mangaluru: Consumer forum orders three-year imprisonment to Lake View builders
news.para: In case of default of payment of the fine, they shall undergo further imprisonment of six months. Those sentenced are Naveen Cardoza and Ujwal D’Souza, of Marian Infrastructures and landowners William Saldanha, B Gayathri Pai, and Lucy Saldanha.

news.title: Pune civic body to auction properties of over 200 tax defaulters in December
news.para: Even after several notices, these tax defaulters have not paid. The administration has given them time to clear the dues by December 20.

news.title: Many infra projects delayed, partial lifting of curbs on construction work won't help much
news.para: While work related to the construction of flyovers is allowed, the ban on drilling, boring and excavation has defeated the whole purpose of the exemptions, contractors said.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body urges owners to cooperate in digitising records
news.para: To generate digital property cards, residents are required to upload recent property tax payment receipts and electricity bills. The civic body is notifying property owners to keep these documents ready for collection.

news.title: NCLT orders insolvency action against Fort Projects
news.para: Fort Projects is part of Fort Group, one of the leading real estate firms in the city, while Emami Realty, the creditor, is part of Emami Group. Emami Realty also has big projects across the city.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP seals four buildings in DLF 1 for violating building norms
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Manish Yadav said that two buildings were sealed following a complaint was filed at the CM Window and two others for violations of occupation certificate norms.

news.title: Bombay HC sets aside Thane civic body's decision against Sheth Developers
news.para: The HC set aside as “manifestly arbitrary’’ the Corporation’s July 2023 refusal to grant the builder development permission with additional developable space as provided in a 2020 regulation, for its free sale building.

news.title: Favouritism allegations mischievous ploy, sections attempting to delay Dharavi project: DRP
news.para: The Opposition Congress had on Friday alleged that the BJP government is 'benefitting' Adani Group by relaxing norms for the Dharavi redevelopment project in Mumbai.

news.title: Odisha CM to inaugurate two EWS housing projects on November 20
news.para: Developed by Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA) in public private partnership (PPP), the projects have social infrastructure facilities such as neighbourhood shopping centres and community gathering space.

news.title: DDA to register buyers for new scheme from November 24
news.para: DDA officials said on Saturday that the registration for around 28,000 low-income group (LIG) and economic weaker section (EWS) flats to be sold on a first-come- first-serve basis will start on November 24.

news.title: Special town planning schemes near Ahmedabad-Mumbai bullet train stations on anvil
news.para: The initial focus of this endeavour is on drafting fresh town planning schemes for the Sabarmati and Surat stations of the project, with plans to replicate similar schemes for other stations in Gujarat.

news.title: Thrikkakara municipality sent eviction notice to Apple Heights residents
news.para: In the notice sent to the residents’ association of the apartment on October 27, the municipality secretary said the civic body has suffered loss of crores of rupees as they have not received permit fees and tax.
